						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Durvinīta Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that making of (the images of) the <hi rend="italic">Parivāra dēvatās</hi> by Śivarāśi-bhaṭāra, son of Gaṭṭada-bhaṭāra, during the reign of Piḻuduvipati (Pṛithivīpati), the younger brother of Durvinīta (the Gaṅga king). It seems that he also gifted three oil mills to the temple for the purpose of burning lamps.</p>						

						</summary>
